.TH "device_get_devnode" 9 "device_get_devnode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
device_get_devnode \- path of device node file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "const char *" device_get_devnode
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "umode_t *mode "  ","
.BI "kuid_t *uid "  ","
.BI "kgid_t *gid "  ","
.BI "const char **tmp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device
.IP "mode" 12
returned file access mode
.IP "uid" 12
returned file owner
.IP "gid" 12
returned file group
.IP "tmp" 12
possibly allocated string
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return the relative path of a possible device node.
Non-default names may need to allocate a memory to compose
a name. This memory is returned in tmp and needs to be
freed by the caller.
